  Now maintaining bittorrent

*bittorrent-3.3 (25 Sep 2003)

  25 Sep 2003; Patrick Kursawe <phosphan@gentoo.org> bittorrent-3.3.ebuild,
  metadata.xml:
  Version bump as requested in bug 29556

*bittorrent-3.2.1b-r4 (10 Aug 2003)

  10 Aug 2003; Luke-Jr <luke-jr@gentoo.org> bittorrent-3.2.1b-r4.ebuild:
  Now uses virtual/bittorrent; revision bump since it's not compiling anything
  anyway

  01 Aug 2003; Tavis Ormandy <taviso@gentoo.org> bittorrent-3.2.1b-r3.ebuild:
  stable on alpha

  24 Jun 2003; Patrick Kursawe <phosphan@gentoo.org>
  bittorrent-3.2.1b-r3.ebuild:
  Considered stable for x86

*bittorrent-3.2.1b-r3 (10 Jun 2003)

  10 Jun 2003; Patrick Kursawe <phosphan@gentoo.org>
  bittorrent-3.2.1b-r3.ebuild, files/bittorrent-stats-3.2.1b.patch:
  Added stats patch (bug 22214) and hopefully closed bug 22264.
  Kept ~sparc and ~ppc because the changes are quite minor.

  30 May 2003; Jack Morgan <jmorgan@gentoo.org> bittorrent-3.2.1b-r2.ebuild:
  Added ~sparc keyword

  29 May 2003; root <pvdabeel@gentoo.org> bittorrent-3.2.1b-r2.ebuild:
  Added ~ppc keyword

  15 May 2003; Tavis Ormandy <taviso@gentoo.org> bittorrent-3.2.1b-r2.ebuild:
  marking ~alpha

*bittorrent-3.2.1b-r2 (08 May 2003)

  08 May 2003; Patrick Kursawe <phosphan@gentoo.org> 
  bittorrent-3.2.1b-r2.ebuild :
  X support now optional as proposed in bug 20608 by Wayne Davison <gentoo@blorf.net>
  and removed unnecessary patch

*bittorrent-3.2.1b-r1 (07 May 2003)

  07 May 2003; Patrick Kursawe <phosphan@gentoo.org>
  bittorrent-3.2.1b-r1.ebuild, files/bittorrent-3.2.1b.patch:
  Patch supplied in bug #20524 - should fix some overflows and
  problems with progress bar. Thanks to Denis Braekhus
  <denis@startsiden.no> for finding it.

